Full Stack Java Development Course Syllabus

Full Stack Java Development Course

  • Core Java
  • HTML, CSS, JS Brushup
  • MySql
  • JPA,Hibernate
  • Spring Boot
  • REST API’s

Core Java

  1. introduction to java
  2. intallation of java in window and Mac
  3. Data type and operators
  4. writing first java program
  5. introduction to class
  6. control statement (For, While, Do-While, For-Each etc.)
  7. Array (Single Dimension, Multi-Dimension).
  8. Object Oriented Programming Concepts.
    1. Encapsulation
    2. Data Hiding
    3. Abstraction
    4. Polymorphism
    5. Inheritance
    6. Constructor
    7. singleton pattern
  9. Exception Handling
    1. Checked vs Unchecked Exception
    2. Handling Exception using try-catch
    3. throws keyword
    4. finally block
    5. Custom Exceptions
  10. Collection Framework
    1. Introduction
    2. Different Interfaces of Collection
    3. Methods of Collection
    4. Methods of List Interface
    5. Methods of Set interface
    6. Methods of Queue Interface
    7. Intro to ArrayList, LinkedList, Vector, Stack, their methods and constructors
    8. Intro to HashSet, LinkedHashSet, TreeSet
    9. Intro to PriorityQueue, BlockingQueue
    10. Intro to Map interface and its methods
    11. Intro. to HashMap, LinkedHashMap and TreeMap
    12. Iterators in Collection
    13. comparable and comparator

Selenium

  1. Introduction to Selenium
  2. Components of Selenium: IDE, RC, WebDriver, Grid
  3. Introduction to WebDriver
  4. WebDriver interface and its methods.
  5. How to launch different browsers using Selenium
  6. Launching url
  7. Introduction to WebElements
  8. Finding WebElements using different locator strategies
  9. Introduction to XPATH:
    1. Absolute vs Relative XPATH
    2. Writing Dynamic XPATH
    3. XPATH functions
    4. XPATH Axeses
  10. Introduction to CSSSelector
    1. Functions of CSSSelector
    2. Different symbols of CSSSelector
  11. Handling Radio buttons, Checkboxes, links and buttons
  12. Handling dropdown using Select class
  13. Handling Windows and Frames
  14. Handling Alerts and Popups
  15. Waits in Selenium (Implicit and Explicit)
  16. Handling Mouse and Keyboard actions
  17. Robot class
  18. Exceptions of Selenium
  19. Taking Screenshot using AShot and Selenium
  20. File upload and download using Autolt

TestNG

  1. Introduction to TestNG
  2. Different annotations of TestNG
  3. Introduction to textng.xml file
  4. Different parameters of @Test annotation
  5. Writing first testcase
  6. Failing first test case
  7. Assertions (SoftAssert and Hard Assert)
  8. Creating dependency (Hard Dependancy and Soft Dependancy)
  9. Groups in TestNG
  10. Parameterization in TestNG
  11. DataProvider in TestNG
  12. Providing data from Excel, CSV and properties file
  13. Cross browser Testing
  14. Taking screenshot when test fails
  15. Different Listeners in TestNG

Cucumber 5

  1. Introduction to BDD
  2. Story of 3 amigos
  3. Installation of Cucumber
  4. Different Gherkin keywords
  5. Writing StepDefinitions
  6. Cucumber Expressions:
    1. Parameter types
    2. Custom Parameter types
    3. Optional text
    4. Alternative text
  7. Checking Assertions
  8. Data Tables
  9. Hooks
  10. Tags
  11. Cucumber Reporting
  12. Integration of Extent Report with Cucumber 5
